{
  "texts": [
    "Hence there is some world v such that wR i v and M, v ⊨ ψ.",
    "Let M ′ be the model based on F that differs from M only in that p M ′ = {v}.",
    "Then since ψ does not contain p, we still have M ′, v ⊨ ψ.",
    "Now observe that the antecedent of (Split) is true at w in M ′, but clearly the consequent of (Split) is false since p M ′ is a singleton set.Worlds cannot split, but possibilities can.",
    "We will construct a full possibility frame that validates an instance of (Split) and ♢ i ψ."
  ]
}